  1996. This submission is without any merit. In our opinion,

  the expression “laws of India” as used in <a href="/doc/846967/" id="a_87">Article 32.1</a> and

  <a href="/doc/1566826/" id="a_88">32.2</a> have a reference only to the contractual obligations to

  be performed by the parties under the substantive contract

  i.e. PSC. In other words, the provisions contained in 33.12
<span class="hidden_text" id="span_46">                                                        39</span>

